pabloysangregorio.dominicos.es |date= |accessdate=2014-05-25}}</ref> He was also professor at the [[Valencia Catholic University Saint Vincent Martyr|Faculty of Theology of Valencia Catholic University Saint Vincent]] and since 1996 is being a professor of Church History in the [[Convent of St. Stephen, Salamanca|Faculty of UPSA of Convent of St. Stephen]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fatse.org/profesor.asp?Id=3 |accessdate=January 3, 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120305151643/http://www.fatse.org/profesor.asp?Id=3 |archivedate=March 5, 2012 }}</ref> and the [[Pontifical University of Salamanca|Faculty of Theology of the Pontifical University of Salamanca]]. He also teaches specialized courses in [[Pontifical University of Salamanca|Faculty of Philosophy of the Pontifical University of Salamanca]] .<ref>[http://www.upsa.es/launiversidad/informacion/institucion/index.php Pontifical University of Salamanca] On September 25, 1940, Pope [[Pius XII]] restored the Faculties of Theology and Canon Law at another university, completely new and independent of [[University of Salamanca]], the [[Pontifical University of Salamanca]]</ref> of the same university. He is Librarian of [[Convent of St. Stephen, Salamanca|Convent of St. Stephen]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fatse.org/facultad/autoridades.asp |accessdate=January 3, 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120131121032/http://www.fatse.org/facultad/autoridades.asp |archivedate=January 31, 2012 }}</ref> and Technical Director of the Internet School of Theology \"Santo Tom\u00e1s de Aquino\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://sanpabloysangregorio.dominicos.es/mision/instituto-superior-de-filosofia |title=Instituto Superior de Filosof\u00c3a - Convento de San Pablo y San Gregorio - Dominicos - Valladolid |publisher=Sanpabloysangregorio.dominicos.es |date= |accessdate=2014-05-25}}</ref>\n\nIn 2008 he was appointed [[Liste of Members of the Royal Academy of Doctors of Spain|Corresponding Member of the Royal Academy of Doctors of Spain]].<ref>[http://www.dominicos.org/verAlbum.aspx?album=4 News and photo of the inauguration of the Academic of the Royal Academy of Doctors of Spain, in the Department of Theology (In Spanish)]</ref><ref>[http://antiguosalumnosdominicos.blogia.com/2008/101601-p.-angel-martinez-casado.php Quote from Angel Martinez Casado on the appointment of Academic Royal Academy of Doctors of Spain, Section of Theology,(In Spanish) October 21, 2008 16:16.]</ref> Has also served as Vice Postulator of the Ecclesiastical Court in charge of the diocesan canonization of Mother Teresa Maria de Jesus Ortega Pardo, the former [[prioress]] of [[Monastery of the Mother of God (Olmedo)|Olmedo Monastery]],<ref>[http://www.archivalladolid.org/nuevo/documento.php?Clave=200607DD]</ref> process which closed on July 18, 2006.\n\n== Bibliography ==\n\n=== Books ===\n\nHis books have been, among others in order of publication:\n\n* 1994, ''EDITORIAL SAN ESTEBAN'', Title: '''Lope de Barrientos : Un Intellectual de la Corte de Juan II'''(Lope de Barrientos: An Intellectual Court Juan II), [http://www.iberlibro.com/products/isbn/9788487557859/757204176][http://yufind.library.yale.edu/yufind/Record/3833168], [[Salamanca]], {{ISBN|84-87557-85-6}}\n* 2006, ''EDITORIAL SAN ESTEBAN'', Title: '''Domingo de Soto: La causa de los pobres'''(Domingo de Soto: The cause of the poor), [http://www.sanestebaneditorial.com/descargas/catalogo2009.pdf][http://yufind.library.yale.edu/yufind/Record/7775724], [[Salamanca]], {{ISBN|84-8260-182-2}}\n\n=== Publishing Error Fe ===\n\n* 2003, SAN ESTEBAN EDITORIAL Title:'''Pe\u00f1a de Francia: Historia, arte, entorno'''(Rock of France: History, art, environment), [http://www.sanestebaneditorial.com/libro.aspx?id=311], ISBN Although 84-8260-125-3 attributed to Angel Mart\u00ednez Casado, actually wrote another Dominican of the same convent, Angel Perez Casado.\n\n=== Articles en magazines ===\n\n* 1976, Magazine ''[[